data.text:
When Oscar Bjork was born on 31 March 1889, in Pine City, Pine, Minnesota, United States, his father, Benjamin Bjork, was 23 and his mother, Hanna Halvorsen, was 25. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Edith J Grant. He lived in Pine City Township, Pine, Minnesota, United States for about 10 years. He died on 17 July 1950, in Saint Paul, Ramsey, Minnesota, United States, at the age of 61, and was buried in Saint Paul, Ramsey, Minnesota, United States.

The first of many consumer protection laws which ban foreign and interstate traffic in mislabeled food and drugs. It requires that ingredients be placed on the label.
